The [[national language]]s of [[Seychelles]] are [[Seychellois Creole]], [[English language|English]] and [[French language|French]].

Seychellois Creole, a [[French-based creole language]], is by far the most commonly spoken language in the archipelago and is spoken natively by about 95% of the population. Nevertheless, the country was a [[British Empire|British colony]] for over a century and a half, and the legacy of [[History of Seychelles#British rule|British Seychelles]]) made English remain the main language in government and business.

French was introduced before the British rule. It has remained in use largely because it is used by the [[Franco-Seychellois]] minority and is similar to Seychellois Creole.

